Eamonn Roche https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eamonn_Roche 0 Eamonn Roche (born February 29, 1968) is an American film and television actor. One of nine siblings, his father was actor Eugene Roche. One of his brothers, Brogan Roche, is an actor; another, Sean Roche, is a director. He appeared with Jim Carrey in the film The Mask. He has appeared on such television programs such as NCIS, General Hospital, Scrubs, Deadwood, Cold Case, Without a Trace, NYPD Blue, Beverly Hills, 90210, Diagnosis: Murder, ER, Crossing Jordan, Walker, Texas Ranger, Babylon 5, Murder, She Wrote, Sabrina the Teenage Witch and Doogie Howser, M.D. Eamonn_Roche ( born February_29_,_1968 ) is an_American_film_and_television_actor .
